title: Live coverage: SpaceX scrubs Sunday Starlink launch in final minute; targets Monday launch opportunity
summary: SpaceX called an abort 46 seconds prior to launching its Falcon 9 rocket from NASA's Kennedy Space Center. Liftoff of the Starlink 10-7 mission is now set for 6:37 a.m. EDT (1037 UTC).

title: Launch Roundup: Starlink constellation continues to expand while China begins building G60 constellation
summary: Following a busy last two weeks, the pace of the worldwide launch schedule is slowing down this week. The first launch of the week will see China launch the initial batch of its G60 internet satellite constellation. If the plans for this expansive constellation are fulfilled, we can expect to see many more of these launches in the near future.
